Download the latest version of python from https://www.python.org/downloads/
Please note that in future if you refer this notes the version might be different than this but while creating this file I downloaded the latest verison of python i.e. 3.9.0
Once downloaded > Install it > Make sure you check the box for "Add Python 3.9 to PATH"
Next we are going to download Code Editor
We are going to use PyCharm Code Editor and you can get it from https://www.jetbrains.com/pycharm
Download the community version of PyCharm which is freely available
